The paper deals with abnormal event detection in video, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an unsupervised feature learning framework and a supervised classification approach, which involves clustering and classification, respectively. These techniques are commonly used in machine learning, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with motion and appearance information, which are important aspects of multimedia analysis, suggesting that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves outlier detection, which is a common problem in information retrieval, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
